main event: Two unidentified objects were observed in Duluth, Minnesota on 16 August 1966 for a duration of 5 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were described as having changing red lights., The witness reported that the objects moved behind clouds during observation., The weather was clear, providing good visibility for the sighting., There were no photographs or physical evidence captured in relation to the sighting., The witness estimated that the objects were about 1 mile away from their location.
sighted object: Two unidentified flying objects with changing red lights
witness description: A female witness who reported the sighting to the Air Force.
